cte elementary education stanford university school of education skip to main content skip to main navigation stanford university school of education home suse directory library axess make a gift stanford home search this site about suse admissions academics faculty & research news & events knowledge at work home academics doctoral programs curriculum studies and teacher education cte cte elementary education cte elementary education the elementary education specialization is designed for students interested in exploring and contributing to scholarship and teaching related to issues of pedagogy curriculum design and implementation school reform equity and equality as they relate to elementary schools classrooms and educators the specialization aims to prepare scholars practitioners and leaders to address a range of important questions in the field of elementary education and elementary teacher education the stanford university school of education includes a number of faculty whose scholarship and teaching take place in the context of elementary schools and classrooms and who have an interest in and enthusiasm for cultivating scholars in the field of elementary education students collaborate closely with faculty on research teaching and the design of their graduate programs our home in stanford's school of education enables students to appreciate the myriad connections between elementary education and the full range of disciplinary specializations and research foci of the school's faculty students also make good use of the wider resources available at stanford routinely enrolling in courses across the university admission depends on a combination of factors including successful teaching or related experience strong academic achievement professional accomplishments gre scores and the fit between student interests and background on the one hand and faculty availability and research areas on the other elementary education faculty maren aukerman claude goldenberg connie 